                            <p><b>*   Ashtanga-style yoga</b>  means eight limbs or branches of yoga mentioned in the Yoga Sutras of Patanjali, of which asana or physical yoga posture is merely one branch, breath or pranayama is another. 
                                Both Pattabhi Jois and Sharath Jois, his grandson, encourage practice of Ashtanga Yoga - all eight limbs.<br />
                                <b>*</b>  "The purpose of vinyasa is for internal cleansing" ("Ashtanga Yoga"). 
                                Synchronizing breathing and movement in the asanas heats the blood, cleaning and thinning it so that it may circulate more freely. 
                                Improved blood circulation relieves joint pain and removes toxins and disease from the internal organs.
                            </p>
                            <ul type="circle">
                                <li><h3><b>The 8 Limbs of Yoga</b></h3></li>
                                    <li><b>YAMA</b> - Restraints, moral disciplines or moral vows.</li>
                                   <li> <b>NIYAMA</b> - Positive duties or observances.</li>
                                   <li> <b>ASANA </b>- Posture.</li>
                                   <li><b> PRANAYAMA</b> - Breathing techniques.</li>
                                   <li><b> PRATYAHARA</b> - Sense withdrawal.</li>
                                   <li><b> DHARANA</b> - Focused concentration.</li>
                                   <li><b> DHYANA</b> - Meditative absorption.</li>
                                   <li><b> SAMADHI</b> - Bliss or enlightenment.</li>
                            
                            
